Preparation and working through different phases of Master's thesis/project; supervisor's seminars, self-reflection as well feedback seminars. Oral or poster presentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Ethnology Seminar is a 3rd semester Master's Seminar. The aim of this course is to provide a student with necessary methodological support to complete her Master's thesis/project.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of this course, the student: - makes adequate theoretical and methodological choices to solve her research problem(s);
- is able to methodologically prepare and conduct her research project;
- uses adequate disciplinary and applied representations of her research project;
- has obtained skills to give feedback in both oral or written form, and to analyses feedback to her research/presentation;
- has a reflective approach toward her research experience and effectively plans new activities related to her project.
